            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-05-04T18:00:00-05:00" n="638" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On September 28, 1948, in connection with the European Recovery Program, the
                    United States and Portugal signed at Lisbon an Economic Cooperation Agreement.
                    For text, see Department of State Treaties and Other International Acts Series
                        (<gloss target="#t_TIAS1">TIAS</gloss>) No. 1819, or 62 Stat. (pt. 3) 2856.
                    Documents relating to negotiation of the Agreement are in Department of State
                    file No. 840.50 Recovery.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
